Copenhagen - Six people including two adults and four children were Monday found dead in a house in western Denmark, police said.Police have cordoned off a large area at the house near the town of Randers, but have not released any details or a motive.Local media reports suggested the deaths were linked to a family tragedy. The local municipal authority said it has activated a crisis plan for affected schools, the local newspaper Aarhus Stiftstidende reported.Dog patrols as well as forensic experts were deployed at the scene. DPA